sub_title: PhD candidate in Computational Biology studying immunotherapy and immune-oncology in urothelial cancer at the Netherlands Cancer Institute | Bioinformatics MSc | Physics BSc | Chemistry BSc
summary:
As a curious bioinformatics scientist with molecular biology expertise, I aim to understand why some tumors do not respond to treatment by employing data science and statistical methodologies to seek answers to these questions. I expect to complete my dissertation by the end of 2023.
Beyond my academic pursuits, I organized diversity and inclusion awareness campaigns and scientific seminars at the Netherlands Cancer Institute and contributed to disseminating DEI (diversity, equity, inclusion) and scientific divulgation at the Association of Spanish Scientists in the Netherlands. 
On my daily life, I enjoy participating in cultural and community-driven activities, practicing meditation and fitness, experiencing live music, experimenting with illustration tools, and traveling.
